<p>Indianapolis residents benefit from several attractive incentives for solar and HVAC upgrades. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit for solar installations through 2032, then decreases to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to the full system cost including equipment, installation, and permitting fees. Indiana offers additional property tax exemptions for renewable energy systems, meaning solar panels won't increase property tax assessments despite adding home value.</p>

