<p>Suburban neighborhoods like Geist and Carmel (technically outside Indianapolis but served by similar utilities) feature newer construction with better insulation and modern electrical systems, making them ideal for both solar panels and high-efficiency HVAC systems. These areas often have optimal roof orientations and minimal shading. Downtown neighborhoods including Mass Ave and Fountain Square present unique challenges with row houses and limited roof space, making community solar programs or innovative mounting solutions attractive alternatives. Westside neighborhoods like Speedway offer excellent solar potential with many ranch-style homes featuring south-facing roofs ideal for panel installation.</p>

